3. cs.SE - The paper deals with system behavior and repair, which are relevant to software engineering. 
4. cs.SY - The paper discusses the use of a hierarchical system specification to make repair plans tractable for large systems, which is relevant to systems engineering. 
5. cs.PL - The paper discusses the tradeoff between simply replacing a component and decomposing it to repair its subcomponents, which is relevant to programming languages and software design.
